    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="466"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/6–2249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-22">June 22,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received June 22—6:02 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1346. Local press June 20 reports Chang Lan, Shih Liang, Lo Lung-chi, “Wang
                    Pao-chang, Kuo Chen-tao,<note n="38" xml:id="d466fn38">All Democratic League
                        members; they reached Peiping on June 24.</note> others arrived in Nanking
                    June 19 on way to Peiping. Chang, Lo, Shih, press states, aside from attending
                    preparatory committee of new PCC will also attend fourth plenary session of
                    Democratic League.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Peiping 231, Shanghai 739, OffEmb Canton
                    unnumbered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
